                  <bindingDesc resp="#BCBB">
                     <binding notAfter="1500" notBefore="1400">
                        <p>15th century, <placeName key="place_1000080">Italian</placeName>, <placeName key="place_7018159">Venice</placeName>? (contemporary with manuscript, 1462, Brescia): wood boards; 
                           light brown leather, blind-tooled with multiple lines, stamps and strapwork; spine original, cross-hatched with blind triple lines and a small flower stamp; traces of four 
                           strap-and-pin clasps running from grooves at front-cover edges to pins at back, all lost; edges plain. Gilt red-leather spine-label and lettering added, 18th century, Italian; 
                           spine, corners and covers clumsily repaired in similar leather, 18th century (Italian) or 19th century (Bodleian)
                           </p>
                     </binding>
